Package: likelyr
Title: Modular Tools for Integrated Likelihood Inference
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person(
      given = "Timothy",
      family = "Ruel",
      email = "timruel88@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre"),
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-1916-5003")
    )
Description: 
    A modular, extensible framework for computing integrated likelihoods (IL) 
    under a zero-score expectation (ZSE) parameterization for arbitrary statistical 
    models and scalar parameters of interest. The package decomposes IL computation 
    into reusable components: model specifications, parameter-of-interest (psi) mappings,
    ZSE parameter sampling, expected log-likelihood closures, constrained nuisance parameter
    optimization via augmented Lagrangians, branch maximization and expansion, and 
    log-sum-exp averaging for Monte Carlo integral approximation. Includes a simulation 
    engine for comparing IL and profile likelihood (PL) estimators. Designed for research, 
    teaching, and reproducible statistical methodology development.
